    {
      "lc": 1,
      "type": "constructor",
      "id": [
        "langchain",
        "schema",
        "messages",
        "ToolMessage"
      ],
      "kwargs": {
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "{\"success\":true,\"process_rule_id\":\"J09D\",\"process_rule\":\"1. Copy decision table into table J09D_temp where the tour starts with J09D.\\n2. Add ENTSCHEIDUNG column.\\n3. Classify meter reading type. Apply rules: 1. Set ENTSCHEIDUNG to \\\"KSA\\\" when a HAUS has less than 3 EQUNR. ELSE set ENTSCHEIDUNG to \\\"EVU\\\". 2. SET all houses with HOUSE_NUM1 of 0 to \\\"EVU\\\". 3. SET all houses with HOUSE_NUM1 500 - 599 to \\\"EVU\\\". 4. SET all houses with HOUSE_NUM1 900 - 999 to \\\"EVU\\\". 5. SET all houses with address area Wiblingwerde or Breckerfeld to \\\"EVU\\\".\\n4. JOIN table with EABLG table using INSTALLATION.\\n5. JOIN table with SALES_MASTER and NET_MASTER table using EQUNR.\\n6. Compare customer sales master data and net master data.\\n7. Check if sales customer data is NOT empty.\\n    If yes: Use sales customer data table entries.\\n    Else: Use net data customer table entries.\\n8. Identify households with mandatory meter reading. Set ENTSCHEIDUNG to \\\"MANDATORY_READING\\\", for every EQUNR in EABL where both ISTABLART_TXT = \\\"Maschinelle Schätzung - SAP\\\" and the Record created on 2024 and ISTABLART_TXT = \\\"Maschinelle Schätzung - SAP\\\" and the Record created on 2023.\\n9. Export these households to CSV. Export all MANDATORY_READING entries from the final table as CSV file named J09D_MANDATORY_READING including the columns: `Meter Reading (MR) Doc. No.`, `HAUS`, `ANLAGE`, `ME_MA_ID`, `EQUNR`, `HOUSE_NUM1`, `ENTSCHEIDUNG`, `TITLE`, `FORENAME`, `SURNAME`, `STREET`, `STREETNO`, `POST_CODE1`, `CITY1`, `CITY2`, `EMAIL`.\\n10. Send them to the internal team. email_address: mandatory.reading@provider.com file_path: <file path for J09D_MANDATORY_READING.csv here>.\\n11. Identify trustworthy households for meter reading self-report. Set ENTSCHEIDUNG to \\\"DIRECT_MAIL\\\", for every EQUNR in EABL where ISTABLART_TXT = \\\"Ablesung durch Kunden - SAP\\\" in 2024 and ISTABLART_TXT = \\\"Ablesung durch Kunden - SAP\\\" in 2023.\\n12. Export these trustworthy households to CSV. Export all DIRECT_MAIL entries from the final table as CSV file named J09D_DIRECT_MAIL including the columns: `Meter Reading (MR) Doc. No.`, `HAUS`, `ANLAGE`, `ME_MA_ID`, `EQUNR`, `HOUSE_NUM1`, `ENTSCHEIDUNG`, `TITLE`, `FORENAME`, `SURNAME`, `STREET`, `STREETNO`, `POST_CODE1`, `CITY1`, `CITY2`, `EMAIL`.\\n13. Send bulk email to all of the DIRECT_MAIL households. Upload the file to send_bulk_mail service for sending direct emails to all the customers.\\n14. Export the final data except the MANDATORY_READING and DIRECT_MAIL. Export the final data except MANDATORY_READING and DIRECT_MAIL entries from the table as CSV file named J09D including the columns: `Meter Reading (MR) Doc. No.`, `HAUS`, `ANLAGE`, `ME_MA_ID`, `EQUNR`, `HOUSE_NUM1`, `ENTSCHEIDUNG`, `TITLE`, `FORENAME`, `SURNAME`, `STREET`, `STREETNO`, `POST_CODE1`, `CITY1`, `CITY2`, `EMAIL`.\\n15. Send email with the CSV file to EVU. Email address meter.readings@evu.com file_path: <path_to_exported_csv_file>.\\n16. Delete temporary table.\"}",
            "id": "lc_73f508e0-8add-48ab-a4b1-35358088c0d4"
          }
        ],
        "type": "tool",
        "name": "retrieve_process",
        "id": "dc0173d4-d668-4b68-b5f1-c968b339e844",
        "tool_call_id": "call_hr69vnp9",
        "artifact": {
          "structured_content": {
            "success": true,
            "process_rule_id": "J09D",
            "process_rule": "1. Copy decision table into table J09D_temp where the tour starts with J09D.\n2. Add ENTSCHEIDUNG column.\n3. Classify meter reading type. Apply rules: 1. Set ENTSCHEIDUNG to \"KSA\" when a HAUS has less than 3 EQUNR. ELSE set ENTSCHEIDUNG to \"EVU\". 2. SET all houses with HOUSE_NUM1 of 0 to \"EVU\". 3. SET all houses with HOUSE_NUM1 500 - 599 to \"EVU\". 4. SET all houses with HOUSE_NUM1 900 - 999 to \"EVU\". 5. SET all houses with address area Wiblingwerde or Breckerfeld to \"EVU\".\n4. JOIN table with EABLG table using INSTALLATION.\n5. JOIN table with SALES_MASTER and NET_MASTER table using EQUNR.\n6. Compare customer sales master data and net master data.\n7. Check if sales customer data is NOT empty.\n    If yes: Use sales customer data table entries.\n    Else: Use net data customer table entries.\n8. Identify households with mandatory meter reading. Set ENTSCHEIDUNG to \"MANDATORY_READING\", for every EQUNR in EABL where both ISTABLART_TXT = \"Maschinelle Schätzung - SAP\" and the Record created on 2024 and ISTABLART_TXT = \"Maschinelle Schätzung - SAP\" and the Record created on 2023.\n9. Export these households to CSV. Export all MANDATORY_READING entries from the final table as CSV file named J09D_MANDATORY_READING including the columns: `Meter Reading (MR) Doc. No.`, `HAUS`, `ANLAGE`, `ME_MA_ID`, `EQUNR`, `HOUSE_NUM1`, `ENTSCHEIDUNG`, `TITLE`, `FORENAME`, `SURNAME`, `STREET`, `STREETNO`, `POST_CODE1`, `CITY1`, `CITY2`, `EMAIL`.\n10. Send them to the internal team. email_address: mandatory.reading@provider.com file_path: <file path for J09D_MANDATORY_READING.csv here>.\n11. Identify trustworthy households for meter reading self-report. Set ENTSCHEIDUNG to \"DIRECT_MAIL\", for every EQUNR in EABL where ISTABLART_TXT = \"Ablesung durch Kunden - SAP\" in 2024 and ISTABLART_TXT = \"Ablesung durch Kunden - SAP\" in 2023.\n12. Export these trustworthy households to CSV. Export all DIRECT_MAIL entries from the final table as CSV file named J09D_DIRECT_MAIL including the columns: `Meter Reading (MR) Doc. No.`, `HAUS`, `ANLAGE`, `ME_MA_ID`, `EQUNR`, `HOUSE_NUM1`, `ENTSCHEIDUNG`, `TITLE`, `FORENAME`, `SURNAME`, `STREET`, `STREETNO`, `POST_CODE1`, `CITY1`, `CITY2`, `EMAIL`.\n13. Send bulk email to all of the DIRECT_MAIL households. Upload the file to send_bulk_mail service for sending direct emails to all the customers.\n14. Export the final data except the MANDATORY_READING and DIRECT_MAIL. Export the final data except MANDATORY_READING and DIRECT_MAIL entries from the table as CSV file named J09D including the columns: `Meter Reading (MR) Doc. No.`, `HAUS`, `ANLAGE`, `ME_MA_ID`, `EQUNR`, `HOUSE_NUM1`, `ENTSCHEIDUNG`, `TITLE`, `FORENAME`, `SURNAME`, `STREET`, `STREETNO`, `POST_CODE1`, `CITY1`, `CITY2`, `EMAIL`.\n15. Send email with the CSV file to EVU. Email address meter.readings@evu.com file_path: <path_to_exported_csv_file>.\n16. Delete temporary table."
          }
        },
        "status": "success"
      }
    },
